org.tensorics.core.math.structures

Interface Structure<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the elements of the mathematical structure
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AbelianGroup<T>, CommutativeMonoid<T>, CommutativeSemigroup<T>, Field<T>, FiniteStructure<T>, Group<T>, GrouplikeStructure<T>, Magma<T>, Monoid<T>, OrderedField<T>, Ring<T>, RinglikeStructure<T>, Semigroup<T>, Semiring<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAbelianGroup, AbstractOrderedField, DoubleField

    public interface Structure<T>
    The base interface for all algebraic structures. A basic property of an mathematical structure is always a set of elements. Since there can be infinite and finite structures, it does not always make sense (or is impossible) to explicitly state the involved set.
    See Also:
    http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_structure
